CM_ BU_ BCM_Gp "Body Control Module, Lear BCM Without TPMS and with HCM, Atlas 3R2

Node type - Type 3, OSEK, Local / Network wake-up 

This variant has 12 LIN bues";
CM_ BU_ BECM "Battery Energy Control Module - EVA2 MHEV";
CM_ BU_ EPICD "EPICD: DCDC Converter MHEV - EVA2";
CM_ BU_ EPICD_E "EPICD: DCDC Converter MHEV - EVA2";
CM_ BU_ GWM "XCL Gateway Module for EVA2, NCR17Q4 / Feature Bundle 3 onwards
";
CM_ BU_ HVAC "Heating Ventilation & Air Conditioning with High Speed Comfort CAN Interfaces";
CM_ BU_ PCM "PCM for Diesel MHEV Engines (PCM_N2)";
CM_ BU_ SGCM "Starter / Generator Control Module.

MHEV 48V BISG";
CM_ BU_ TSTR "Offboard Tester with High Speed Comfort CAN Interface - TSTR_HS";
CM_ SG_ 103 EPBBrakeApplyReq "This is the request from the EPB system for the SCS to apply the main vehicle brakes.
This is to prevent excessive wear of the EPB linings.
";
CM_ SG_ 103 EPBDecelerationTarget "This is the Electric Park Brake target deceleration value.";
CM_ SG_ 103 EPBFault "Indicates if there is a fault with the Electric Park Brake.";
CM_ SG_ 103 EPBSignalCounter "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.
It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.
Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
CM_ SG_ 103 EPBStatus_EUCD "To inform the BCM (brake control) about Rear caliper ststus and if EPB system is active or inactive

For details see SRD 31815888 or ECU SWRS
";
CM_ SG_ 103 EPBStatusChecksum "This CRC shall be calculated in compliance with STJLR 18.036 Version 5.
The Data Segment Polynomial shall be constructed from the details
in the network configuration file.";
CM_ SG_ 103 KeepNetInAfterRunPBM "CAN signal stating if the network is required for After-Run.

Description of bit field detailing each application function to be stored in the DID (After-Run Function 1- 16):
Bit 0: Brake Temperature
Bit 1-15: Unused";
CM_ SG_ 19 GSAAliveCounter "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.
It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.
Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
CM_ SG_ 19 GSAChecksum "This CRC shall be calculated in compliance with STJLR 18.036 Version 5.
The Data Segment Polynomial shall be constructed from the details in the network configuration file.";
CM_ SG_ 19 GSAFaults "Display GSM Faults
xxxx xxx1 Single Bit Position Sensor Fault
xxxx xx1x Multiple Bit Position Sensor Fault
xxxx x1xx Park Button Stuck
xxxx 1xxx Position Display Fault
xxx1 xxxx Unlock Button Stuck
xx1x xxxx Buttons Electrical Fault
x1xx xxxx Lever Lock/Flipback Fault
1xxx xxxx Ignition Status";
CM_ SG_ 19 GSAPosReq "Final arbitrated gear position as arbitrated by GSA.";
CM_ SG_ 19 GSAPosReqOrigin "Describes how the Transmission Range Request (P,R,N,D,S) transmitted on the signal GSAPosReq was generated";
CM_ SG_ 19 GSAPosReqRepeat "To send repeat request to engage gear requested by GSAPosReq";
CM_ SG_ 19 GSAWarning "Alerts Request Signal originating in GSM. Passed through and modified slightly by GSA to become GSAWarning.

More then one bit to can be set in the signal. This is to request multiple
messages.
xxxx xxx1 = Gearbox Fault
xxxx xx1x = User error1
xxxx x1xx = User error2
xxxx 1xxx = User error3
xxx1 xxxx = Lock failure
xx1x xxxx = Tip not available
x1xx xxxx = GSM Fault 1
1xxx xxxx = GSM Fault 2";
CM_ SG_ 65 MaxRegenBrkTrqLimRA "Rear axle regen torque limit request signal for BEVs. Enables the regen capacity of the rear axle to be capped.";
CM_ SG_ 65 TotalWheelBrakeTrq2 "Total brake request (driver + system + regen braking) referenced at the wheels. Excludes the effects of individual wheel brake modulation e.g. due to stability events.";
CM_ SG_ 65 WheelBrakeTorqueGpAC "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.

It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.

Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
CM_ SG_ 65 WheelBrakeTorqueGpCS "This CRC shall be calculated in compliance with STJLR 18.036 Version 6.

The Data Segment Polynomial shall be constructed from the details in the network configuration file.";
CM_ SG_ 17 ABSAliveCounter "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.
It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.
Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
CM_ SG_ 17 ABSChecksum "This CRC shall be calculated in compliance with STJLR 18.036 Version 5.
The Data Segment Polynomial shall be constructed from the details
in the network configuration file.";
CM_ SG_ 17 ABSEngVacReq "1 bit signal used to indicate that ABS is unable to generate any/ sufficient brake vacuum using the electric vacuum pump, and that the engine will need to generate brake vacuum itself.";
CM_ SG_ 17 ABSPwrTrnTorqReq "This is a renaming action for ABSReqEngRunning to give clarity of the intent of this signal.
It does not mean that the internal combustion engine must be running, rather it means that the powertrain torque must be available to the driver. This may be achieved by the internal combustion engine, or an e-machine, and the transmission";
CM_ SG_ 17 BrakePressure "Non Hybrid: The signal informs about the pressure in the master cylinder.
Hybrid: Indicates the pressure that would be present at the master cylinder for the same total
brake torque delivered by the HEV braking system compared to a conventional braking system.

Note: The signal saturates at 204.6 bar. The actual brake pressure can exceed 204.6 bar.";
CM_ SG_ 17 BrakePressureQF "Quality factor for the signal BrakePressure.
";
CM_ SG_ 17 VehicleSpeed "Use in conjunction with VehicleSpeedQF. A value of 65535d may also be set under error conditions.
 
Rear Wheel Drive and AWD Vehicles: VehicleSpeed is calculated as the average speed of the two driven rear wheels. If one wheel speed sensor fails, VehicleSpeed will use the speed information from the other sensor.  

Four Wheel Drive Vehicles: VehicleSpeed is calculated as the average speed of all four wheels. In the case of wheel speed sensor failures, VehicleSpeed will use the speed information from the remaining sensors.

Front Wheel Drive and AWD Vehicles: VehicleSpeed is calculated as the average speed of the two driven front wheels. If one wheel speed sensor fails, VehicleSpeed will use the speed information from the other sensor.

Rolling circumference values used in vehicle speed calculation differ per carline.
If you are interested in knowing the rolling circumference values, please contact the ABS team- Tim Reynolds (treyno13)
";
CM_ SG_ 17 VehicleSpeedQF "Quality factor for the signal VehicleSpeed. EuCD compliant signal.";
CM_ SG_ 1281 NMmessageBCMHS "This is the Network Management Protocol Data Unit (NMPDU) for the BCM on HS_CAN.

Description of station manager bit field detailing each application function (station manager function 1-16)
Bit 0 - Power Mode Management
Bit 1 - Start Warnings
Bit 2 - Courtesy Lights
Bit 3 - Alarm and Security
Bit 4 - Passive key scan requests
Bit 5 - Personalisation
Bit 6 - Doors and Windows
Bit 7 - Start Authorisation and ESCL
Bit 8 - Lighting
Bit 9 - Electric Park Brake
Bit 10 - Steering Column Control
Bit 11 - HeVAC
Bit 12 - Trip Computer Button
Bit 13 - Not Used
Bit 14 - Diagnostics
Bit 15 - Not Used

The MSB of the signal must be written to the COM layer first (with an offset of zero in wr_bytes() ) and therefore transmitted on the bus first.
Similarly, subscribing modules will receive the MSB of the signal when they call rd_bytes(0).

E.g. wr_bytes(0) = published_signal_MSB;

Subscribed_Signal_MSB = rd_bytes(0);

";
CM_ SG_ 417 AlarmModeHS "Vehicle Alarm Mode";
CM_ SG_ 417 CabinCleaningWakeUpReq "Signal to trigger the scheduled cabin cleaning after the Timer expired.";
CM_ SG_ 417 CarModeHS "Information about which Carmode the vehicle is in i.e. Normal, factory etc.
";
