CM_ SG_ 417 CLockCmd_2 "Central Locking command to control the latch actuators.

Bitcoded:
CentralLock                   0000 0001
CentralUnlock                0000 0010
CentralDL                       0000 0011
CentralUnlockDL           0000 0100
TrunkLock                     0000 0101
TrunkUnlock                  0000 0110
DDUnlock                      xxx1 1111
PDUnlock                      xx1x 1111
LRUnlock                      x1xx 1111
RRUnlock                      1xxx 1111
DDLock                         xxx1 0000
PDLock                         xx1x 0000
LRLock                         x1xx 0000
RRLock                         1xxx 0000
CrashUnlock                  0000 1000 ";
CM_ SG_ 417 CLockCmd_3 "Central Locking command to control the latch actuators.

Bitcoded:
CentralLock                   0000 0001
CentralUnlock                0000 0010
CentralDL                       0000 0011
CentralUnlockDL           0000 0100
TrunkLock                     0000 0101
TrunkUnlock                  0000 0110
DDUnlock                      xxx1 1111
PDUnlock                      xx1x 1111
LRUnlock                      x1xx 1111
RRUnlock                      1xxx 1111
DDLock                         xxx1 0000
PDLock                         xx1x 0000
LRLock                         x1xx 0000
RRLock                         1xxx 0000
CrashUnlock                  0000 1000 ";
CM_ SG_ 417 PHEVFuelFillRequest "This signal is used on vehicles fitted with sealed fuel systems and a fuel flap sensor i.e. PHEV
This  indicates that the fuel refill button has been pressed inside the passenger compartment.
When the button is pressed the status is latched until the PCM acknowledges and clears down the request.";
CM_ SG_ 417 PowerMode "Information of current PowerMode, reflects the current  state of the Power Mode Superviser

For L538:
The signals PowerModeHS, PowerModeHSQF & PowerModeComp are all with the group PowerModeGrpHS. This grouping is to ensure that the signals are packed within the same frame, they are not treated as a group within the BCM. ";
CM_ SG_ 417 PowerModeAliveCounter "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.
It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.
Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
