CM_ SG_ 744 MVBattCalibrationID01 "Sporadic Signal  - Calibration Identification for the software installed on the ECU. Format is 16 character 128 bit ASCII ($20 through $7E) Each character is 7 bits and is split over two messages. This signal comprises characters 1 to 8 of 16 characters.

128 ASCII (56 bits)
---------------------
Bit 0 to 6 = Character 1 of 16
Bit 7 to 13 = Character 2 of 16
Bit 14 to 20 = Character 3 of 16
Bit 21 to 27 = Character 4 of 16
Bit 28 to 34 = Character 5 of 16
Bit 35 to 41 = Character 6 of 16
Bit 42 to 48 = Character 7 of 16
Bit 49 to 56 = Character 8 of 16
Bit 57 to 63 = Unused";
CM_ SG_ 745 MVBattCalibrationID02 "Sporadic Signal  - Calibration Identification for the software installed on the ECU. Format is 16 character 128 bit ASCII ($20 through $7E) Each character is 7 bits  and is split over two messages. This signal comprises characters 9 to 16 of 16 characters.

128 ASCII (56 bits)
---------------------
Bit 0 to 6 = Character 9 of 16
Bit 7 to 13 = Character 10 of 16
Bit 14 to 20 = Character 11 of 16
Bit 21 to 27 = Character 12 of 16
Bit 28 to 34 = Character 13 of 16
Bit 35 to 41 = Character 14 of 16
Bit 42 to 48 = Character 15 of 16
Bit 49 to 56 = Character 16 of 16
Bit 57 to 63 = Unused";
CM_ SG_ 746 MVBattCalibVerifNumber "Sporadic Signal  - Number used to verify the integrity of the vehicle software. Consists of four Bytes values interpreted as Hexadecimal eg 0B 9F 4E D5

Hexadecimal
Bit Value  Hex Description
--------------------------------------------------------
Bit 0 to 3 (0x0 to 0xF) First Hex value (1st Byte)
Bit 4 to 7 (0x0 to 0xF) Second Hex value (1st Byte)
Bit 8 to 11 (0x0 to 0xF) Third Hex value (2nd Byte)
Bit 12 to 15 (0x0 to 0xF) Forth Hex value (2nd Byte)
Bit 16 to 19 (0x0 to 0xF) Fifth Hex value (3rd Byte)
Bit 20 to 23 (0x0 to 0xF) Sixth Hex value (3rd Byte)
Bit 24 to 27 (0x0 to 0xF) Seventh Hex value (4th Byte)
Bit 28 to 31 (0x0 to 0xF) Eighth Hex value (4th Byte)";
CM_ SG_ 748 MVBattDiagnostic01 "Bit coded Diagnostic message contained in a single CAN signal. Periodically broadcast by component to the Diagnostic Service Manager

Bit 0 = Reserved01
Bit 1 =    STACK_VOLT_CMP [P0B3C-17]  [Stack Voltage]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 2 =    BUS_DCDC_VOLTAGE_MISMATCH [P0E35-62]  [Stack Voltage Sense]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 3 =    BUS_BISG_VOLTAGE_MISMATCH [P0DA8-62]  [Stack Voltage Sense]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 4 =    LVBAT_LO [U3003-16]  [System Voltage]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 5 =    LVBAT_HI [U3003-17]  [System Voltage]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 6 =    SW_5V [P06A3 - 00]  [5 Volt Reference Voltage]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault'
Bit 7 =    HW_OCP_MON [P0D34-00]  [Battery Current]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 8 =    BCC_CURRENT_SENSE [P0ABF-00]  [Battery Current]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 9 =    TEMP1_OOR_Hi [P0A9E-00]  [Battery Temperature]             0 = No Fault ";
CM_ SG_ 749 MVBattDiagnostic02 "Bit coded Diagnostic message contained in a single CAN signal. Periodically broadcast by component to the Diagnostic Service Manager

Bit 0 = Reserved01
Bit 1 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE1  [P3007-1C]  [Voltage Measurement]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 2 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE2 [P3008-1C]  [Voltage Measurement]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 3 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE3 [P3009-1C]  [Voltage Measurement]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 4 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE4 [P300A-1C]  [Voltage Measurement]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 5 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE5 [P300B-1C]  [Voltage Measurement]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 6 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE6 [P300C-1C]  [Voltage Measurement]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 7 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE7 [P300D-1C]  [Voltage Measurement]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 8 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE8 [P300E-1C]  [Voltage Measurement]             0 = No Fault     1 = Fault
Bit 9 =    CELL_OPEN_SENSE9 [P300F-1C]  [Voltage M";
