CM_ SG_ 219 PwrSupSwitchRequest "Signal requesting the PSS (Power Supply System) to actively switch the Dual Battery switches into the ready to crank state.  These switches are used to isolate or bring into circuit both main and secondary 12V batteries.  The signal is reset back to its default state (0) once the engine is running again.  This signal works in conjunction with the acknowledgement CAN signal PwrSupSwitchStatus.";
CM_ SG_ 219 PwrSupSwitchRequestCmp "Signal requesting the PSS (Power Supply System) to actively switch the Dual Battery switches into the ready to crank state.  These switches are used to isolate or bring into circuit both main and secondary 12V batteries.  The signal is reset back to its default state (0) once the engine is running again.  This signal works in conjunction with the acknowledgement CAN signal PwrSupSwitchStatus.

This is a complement signal to provide data integrity across the communication layer.";
