CM_ SG_ 191 CrashAirbagStatus "Driver and passenger airbag deployment status. This information is used to estimate the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashOccClassStatus "Front passenger seat occupancy status. This information is to be considered while estimating the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashPACOSSwitchState "'Passenger Airbag Cut Off Switch' state. This information is to be used while estimating the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashPretensionerStat "Driver's and front seat passenger's pretensioner state. This information is used in estimating the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashSeatBeltBcklState "Driver's and front seat passenger's seatbelt buckle state. This information is used to estimate the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashSeverityClass "Crash severity classification for frontal collisions. Set to 'No event' for rear/side collisions.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashSideAirbagStatus "Side airbags/curtains deployment status. This information is used to estimate the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashStatusPIE "This signal defines the crash status of the PIE.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashStatusRCM "This signal defines the crash status of the vehicle safety system.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashTypeFront "Signal indicates whether front crash has occurred or not. This is required to estimate the crash severity.
0 - No Front crash
1 - Front crash

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashTypeRear "Signal indicates whether rear crash has occurred or not. This is required to estimate the crash severity.
0 - No rear crash
1 - Rear crash

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashTypeRoll "Signal indicates whether vehicle rollover has occurred or not. This information is required to estimate the crash severity.

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.
";
CM_ SG_ 191 CrashTypeSide "Signal indicates whether side crash has occurred or not. This information is required to estimate the crash severity.
0 - No side crash
1 - Side crash 

This signal is used for additional data about the crash event that has occurred when CrashStatusRCM has been set to crash.
The signal status reported here shall represent the status at the point of crash detection and shall be latched in that state for the period that CrashStatusRCM is set to crash.";
CM_ SG_ 191 DrivSeatBeltBcklError "When the bit is set to a '1', a fault condition exists for the driver's seat belt buckle switch.";
CM_ SG_ 191 DrivSeatBeltBcklState "When the bit is set to a '1', the driver's seat belt buckle is latched.
This signal will be invalid and set to 1 (latched) during proveout and should not be used by subscriber until the valid state is established at 1sec post ignition on PM6";
CM_ SG_ 191 DrivSeatPositionError "Error status of driver seat track position switch.";
CM_ SG_ 191 DrivSeatPositionStatus "Status of driver seat track position switch.

This signal will be invalid and set to 1 (forward) during proveout and should not be used by subscribers until the valid state is established at 1sec post ignition on (PM6)";
CM_ SG_ 191 KeepNetInAfterRunRCM "An after-run function master shall send a CAN signal stating that the network is required during after-run. This allows the after-run manager to keep the OSEK nodes awake in order to create a stable ring and also allows supporting slaves to continue CAN transmission or supply ECU power.";
