CM_ SG_ 260 CalcLoadValue "Indicates the percent of peak available torque during normal, fault free driving conditions. Petrol and Diesel engines shall support this message. The diesel calulation is slightly different see ISO 15031-5 for this however the size and scaling is the same.

EuCD signal name
";
CM_ SG_ 260 ChargingKeyScanRes "Provide the result for key search scan if secure key detected";
CM_ SG_ 260 EngineTorqueRipple "The amplitude of torque ripple (1st Harmonic) of the engine.";
CM_ SG_ 260 GearPosActual "Actual gear position.
Note - this signal is not ASIL rated.
If in gliding this signal will read the gear that the transmission would have been in if gliding was not active.

Info: The EV Drive encoding will only be used on powertrain architectures where there is a transmission that doesn't control torque to all the wheels. e.g. D8 PHEV where the transmission controls torque the wheels on the front axle only.";
CM_ SG_ 260 OBDDriveCycle "This signal indicates that the EMS has determined the current drive cycle has met the criteria for a valid OBD drive cycle.  This signal shall be reset to 0 at start-up and shall be latched to 1 when a valid drive cycle has been achieved.
This signal should only be used for OBD diagnostics.

This signal is determined in accordance to: Title 13, California Code Regulations, Section 1968";
CM_ SG_ 260 OBDGeneralDenominator "This signal indicates that the EMS has determined the current drive cycle has been classified as a valid general OBD drive cycle.  This signal must be used to increase the denominator in the calculation of rate based monitors.  This signal shall be reset to 0 at start-up and shall be latched to 1 when the drive cycle is valid.
This signal should only be used for OBD diagnostics.

This signal is determined in accordance to: Title 13, California Code Regulations, Section 1968";
CM_ SG_ 260 OBDWarmUpCycle "This signal indicates that the EMS has determined the current drive cycle has met the criteria for a valid OBD warm up.  This signal shall be reset to 0 at start-up and shall be latched to 1 when a valid warm up cycle is achieved.
This signal should only be used for OBD diagnostics.

This signal is determined in accordance to: Title 13, California Code Regulations, Section 1968";
CM_ SG_ 260 PEChargingInletLockCmd "Passive Entry unlock request for the Plug-In Charging Socket.";
CM_ SG_ 346 ChargeCableUnlockReq "Request to unlock the charge cable by remote mobile app";
CM_ SG_ 346 ChargeFlapActn "Request to actuate power charge flap from remote mobile app";
CM_ SG_ 346 ChargeFlapActnIVI "Request to actuate power charge flap";
CM_ SG_ 346 StatusLightConfig "User configuration of Status light preference";
CM_ SG_ 8 ParkLockDataTarget "CAN signal used by TCM/EDPM to send 'Idle, challenge query' & Enable status to BCM for Start Authorisation.
";
CM_ SG_ 772 CabinCleaningReqTCU "Request for Cabin Cleaning feature Activation.";
CM_ SG_ 772 CabinCleanPreconStatTCU "Status update about Vehicle pre condition checks for remote activation";
CM_ SG_ 772 SlcEvCaReqrdEnergy "Signal giving the required energy consumption value in terms of kWh regardless of maximum battery capacity.";
CM_ SG_ 772 SlcEvCaTargetSoC "This signal indicates the Target SoC value which is required to meet user's energy requirements only for Typical day charge option.";
CM_ SG_ 607 ChargeModeAvailableExt "To restrict the Charge mode change via Charge bowl or remote app or infotainment while vehicle charging in public charging station OR vehicle doesn't have any valid timed charging settings";
CM_ SG_ 607 PairedWKeyId "The identification number of the Key ID for which Ranging needs to be performed.This signal will be set to PkeyId received from RFA in  the case when a Passive Key is used and there is no WK present which is paired with Phone.

Bit7 to Bit0= No PairedKeyID (0000 0000)
Bit0 = PairedKEYID1 (0000 0001)
Bit1 = PairedKEYID2 (0000 0010)
Bit2 = PairedKEYID3 (0000 0100)
Bit3 = PairedKEYID4 (0000 1000)
Bit4 = PairedKEYID5 (0001 0000)
Bit5 = PairedKEYID6 (0010 0000)
Bit6 = PairedKEYID7 (0100 0000)
Bit7 = PairedKEYID8 (1000 0000)";
CM_ SG_ 607 SOTAEstimatedDuration "Estimated installation duration for SOTA install event";
CM_ SG_ 607 SOTAPrepRequest "Request to start preparing subscribing modules for a SOTA installation event";
CM_ SG_ 785 eCallVoiceCallStatus "To receive the status of the voice call";
CM_ SG_ 785 UTCTimeDate "Date and time is based on Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). 

Part:  No of bits     LSB      MSB             Value range        Scaling     Offset

                             offset    offset             Min     -> Max



Year        8               40         47             2000         2254          1          2000

Month      8              32         39                0              12            1             0

Day         8              24          31                0              31            1             0

Hour        8              16          23                0              23            1             0 

Minute     8               8           15                0              59            1             0 

Second   8               0             7                0              59            1             0 

sync        4             48            51              0              15            1             0


LSB/MSB offsets are in Motorola Backwards format, and are of";
CM_ SG_ 546 SetTimer1Time "Signal with Timer1Time

SetTimer1TimeCoding:

Bit/Byte coded:

Byte 1=Month
Byte 2=Day
Byte 3=Hour
Byte 4=Minute
";
CM_ SG_ 547 SetTimer2Time "Signal with Timer2Time

SetTimer2TimeCoding:

Bit/Byte coded:

Byte 1=Month
Byte 2=Day
Byte 3=Hour
Byte 4=Minute
";
CM_ SG_ 80 KeepNetInAfterRunTCM "CAN signal stating if the network is required for After-Run.

Description of bit field detailing each application function to be stored in the DID (After-Run Function 1- 16):
Bit 0: output speed condition (n_ab)
Bit 1: position condition (PosPRND)
Bit 2: timer condition 1(tmr_PowerDown)
Bit 3: timer condition 2 (tmr_PowerDownLong)
Bit 4: SbW Display Timer condition
Bit 5 - 15: Fixwert: 0x00";
CM_ SG_ 80 ReAlignToNeutral "Request from the TCM for the GSM to reset its output of driver request to Neutral
";
CM_ SG_ 80 ReAlignToPark "Request from the TCM for the GSM to reset its output of driver request to Park";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMLockETSReq "Used to Lock ETS for shiftlock functionality and for locking ETS in the event of transmission failure.";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMLockGSMReq "Signal to support the GSA functions., Bit No. Description  (Bit encoded), , Bit 0 - Park at Speed Availability (P Speed lock) , , 0 = P not available , 1 = P Available, , , Bit 1 - LMC Interface Health , , 0 = Faulty , 1 = Healthy, , , Bit 2 - LMC HELD , , 0 = Vehicle not Held , 1 = Vehicle Held, , , Bit 3 - BSCM Interface Health,  , 0 = Faulty , 1 = Healthy";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMLockGSMReqComp "Signal to support the GSA functions., Bit No. Description  (Bit encoded), , Bit 0 - Park at Speed Availability (P Speed lock), , 0 = P Available, 1 = P not available, , , Bit 1 - LMC Interface Health, , 0 = Healthy , 1 = Faulty, , , Bit 2 - LMC HELD, , 0 = Vehicle Held, 1 = Vehicle not Held , , , Bit 3 - BSCM Interface Health, , 0 = Healthy, 1 = Faulty";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMParkReqAck "Used to inform the ETS that the TCM is processing a shift request into Park, used to check validity. Max normal shift time 0.1s. Max Shift time to Park 0.4Sec.";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMPosAliveCounter "This counter forms part of a safety-related signal group.
It is incremented by the task which generates the data set used in the CRC calculation, and may be used to determine the health of the data generation task.
Refer to STJLR 18.036 for more detail.";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMPosChecksum "This CRC shall be calculated in compliance with STJLR 18.036 Version 5.
The Data Segment Polynomial shall be constructed from the details in the network configuration file.";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMPositionDisplay "Message used by IPK and ETS to display selected gear information.TCM will set multiple bits when e.g in Drive 5th gear and in Sport. The Signal TCMDrivingModeDisplay can be used for gear 1-8 display when in manual mode.

Init: Blank ETS display and Blank IPK display. Bit 14 and 15 set to 1, all other bits set to 0 (49152 decimal)

Bits 0 - 5: Gear Selection
000000 = Auto selection
000001 = 1st Gear
000010 = 2nd Gear
000100 = 3rd Gear
001000 = 4th Gear
010000 = 5th Gear
100000 = 6th Gear
100001 = 7th Gear
100010 = 8th Gear
100100 = 9th Gear

Bits 6 - 11: Gear Mode
000001 = Fault
000010 = Park  Position
000100 = Reverse Position
001000 = Neutral Position
010000 = Drive Position
100000 = Sport Position 

Bits 12 - 13: Flash Display
x1 = FLASH ETS Display
1x = FLASH IPK Display

Bits 14 - 15: Blank Display
x1 = Blank ETS Display
1x = Blank IPK Display


On Electronic Shifter installations, the TCMPositionDisplay CAN message will indicate Park as follows:      - at ignition on the";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMStartEnable "Bit is used to inform the ETS that the TCM is a position such that engine crank is permissible. ";
CM_ SG_ 80 TCMText "The code for the current TCM Text message to be displayed. 

EuCD signal name.";
CM_ SG_ 80 TransTICStatus "Used to indicate the status of transmission Idle Control functionality

This signal is provided at a QM rating only";
CM_ SG_ 1736 UUDTBECMResponse1 "Unacknowledged Unsegmented Data Transfer Signal from the BECM to the MCD-Hub data logger. Used for rapid data transfer in compliance with:
Ford GGDS (Generic Global Diagnostic Specification).
ISO 14229
ISO 15765-3.
UUDTBECM1 shall always be packaged into CAN Identifiers 0x6C9

The timing specified within GGDS for frame transfers is:

Slow: 1000ms period
Medium: 100ms period
Fast: Specified by transmitting application supplier.

NOTE: All Volcano Timing Analysis has been performed on this signal at the Medium Rate (100ms). Any attempt to transmit the Message containing this signal at a faster rate may result in unknown delays on the vehicle CAN Bus, which could potentially disrupt normal functionality. In addition, transmission rates faster than Medium cannot be guaranteed.

The MSB of the signal must be written to the COM layer first (with an offset of zero in wr_bytes() ) and therefore transmitted on the bus first.
Similarly, subscribing modules will receive the MSB of the signal when they ca";
